-- Barnes & Noble's retail head sells shares
-- 
-- Mon Aug 26, 2013 9:08pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/08/27/us-barnesandnoble-klipper-idUSBRE97Q01D20130827

 

 (Reuters) - Barnes & Noble Inc's ( BKS.N ) retail group head Mitchell Klipper sold about two-thirds of his shares in the beleaguered retailer in the past few days, according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. 
 Klipper, 55, who has been the chief executive of Barnes & Noble's retail group since March 2010, sold about 400,996 shares at prices ranging from $13.99 to $14.53, raising more than $5.5 million, the filing showed. ( link.reuters.com/fam62v ) As of the company's recent proxy filing dated July 29, Klipper owned 622,000 shares. He is the second-highest paid executive of the company and owns about 1 percent of its outstanding shares. The disclosure comes a week after the largest U.S. bookstore chain's founder and top shareholder, Leonard Riggio, suspended plans to make an offer for the retail business. (Reporting by Avik Das in Bangalore; Editing by Stephen Coates)